
--- Usage ---

In order to use the Logger you MUST do the following:

Register the LoggerIntentService in your manifest:
<service
    android:name="com.sonymobile.userlogginglib
        .service.LoggerService"
    android:enabled="true" android:exported="false" />

Add permission to (read only) access to phone state:
    <uses-permission android:name=
        "android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE" />

Add permission to access information about networks:
    <uses-permission android:name=
        "android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />
        
Add permission to open network sockets:
    <uses-permission android:name=
        "android.permission.INTERNET" />

You need to create a Logger:
    Logger logger = new Logger();

and then call:
    logger.init();

to initialize the Logger, failing to call init()
will result in no logs being sent to the server.

to log some data simply call:
    logger.log().with(key, value).send();
for each log event you want to create and send.